.TH "fscrypt_fname_alloc_buffer" 9 "fscrypt_fname_alloc_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fscrypt_fname_alloc_buffer \- allocate a buffer for presented filenames
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fscrypt_fname_alloc_buffer
.BI "(u32 max_encrypted_len "  ","
.BI "struct fscrypt_str *crypto_str "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "max_encrypted_len" 12
maximum length of encrypted filenames the buffer will be
used to present
.IP "crypto_str" 12
(output) buffer to allocate
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate a buffer that is large enough to hold any decrypted or encoded
filename (null-terminated), for the given maximum encrypted filename length.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
